caption: At the moment  you step in that restaurant  the stuff gives you a great feeling. Very hospitable team, it is a good restaurant to hang out with your friends or with your date. Great  cuisine, qualified  chef de cuisine, honest  price and nice  service. Warmly recommended.
Amazing quality and great Food. Creativity with food is Art!
They never disappoint, five star overall

I wish I would have read the reviews first. We were in the area and decided to try something new. It was exciting to see kool-aid on the menu and thankfully they didn’t go wrong with the blue kool-aid. Overall...we were catfished! The man-n-cheese, honestly no words I can’t even imagine how it was prepared, chick-fil-a’s mac-n-cheese is 30x better. The fries were not the fries from the pic, they were wedges that didn’t taste good at all. My daughter says the fried catfish was good and that was it. Very disappointed, I wish I would have spent my money on calories at the Cheesecake Factory. It is rare that I write a review, but this was a HUGE catfish. Decided to give it a shot with limited reviews thinking it was a new spot. The service was good. I tried calling to speak to manager instead of writing a review and my calls are not connecting to restaurant...”unavailable Verizon customer”.

It's just that of what the name say's, but it's like comfort food with a twist of Upscaledness, with great Upscale foods, and simple downhome beverage's and I think 🤔 of it to be in a great but prime location of PG County within but outside the area of PG Plaza Mall, everyone should come out to see and give a taste of a great Black Owned Business

First time visiting this establishment. I called a couple days before going to see if they would be open the day we wanted to visit. The gentleman stated they would be open that day and that they close at 5:30. I show up at 1:00pm after driving 30 minutes and the place was closed. I keep calling on different days to see if they are open and they are never open at their posted hours.

Didn't even know it was a restaraunt due to the tinted windows (I thought it was an empty office spot) but I was hungry and walked in today for a carryout and wow. WOW. It's like a local IHOP but so much cheaper and so much better.  Anyways yeah it's worth it, food is delicious and strikes a balance of "tasty from a restaurant" but also somewhat...comforting, like home cooking. The server was so friendly and kind too, so sweet, and I'm definitely a fan now. Absolutely recommend if you're looking for comfort food or a midday breakfast (with giant serving portions nonetheless!)  EDIT: (12/11/20) I went in again today and just had to a picture, the pancakes came out big enough to fill the tray and the steak and eggs look so yummy aaaaaa
Fantastic and tasty food, I loved the vibes this place has, and the cashiers were very kind. Will definitely visit here next time.

The food was decent, but there was an issue with them not turning on their system to see mobile orders, so we literally did not get our food until almost two hours after placing our initial order. Additionally, when we tried to call them to make sure they received our order, no one answered the phone on mutiple occasions, which forced us to go to the restaurant only to discover they didn't receive the order because they didn't turn on their ipads.  While the food was decent, it was not worth the wait. That was our first time there, so it was not a good first impression.

Stumbled upon this this place and decided to get breakfast. I ordered the steak and eggs and my partner order the shrimp skillet and lemonade. Despite the fact the fact that they were out of bottled water, the lemonade tasted like mango juice, and the wait was longer than expected. The meals were tasty. Instead of a fried egg I would have like scrambled with cheese instead but the hostess didn't ask (I didn't know there was an option until after the food was served). Home fries were delicious !

After a 6 mile hike, my friends and I (3) decided to switch up our regular Sunday breakfast and walk to some place new. After some recommendations made by the cashier  both of my friends decided to try the Mac and cheese. The Mac and cheese tasted and looked as if it was made days prior as the cheese was separated from the noodle and it tasted as if it was warmed up in a microwave with little cheese added. I tried the steak and eggs, which I requested to be medium. At best the steak was well done and lacked flavour. To say the least I was disappointed, because the pictures on instagram looked very promising. However, the food was not good at all. Definitely false  advertisement. I would recommend looking twice before walking here.
The food was disgusting. How do you mess up a chicken and waffle? They are cutting corners with the Mac and cheese. It tastes like sour cream with a little bit of cheese.
Oh my gosh
The bomb! Definitely reccomend

Excellent establishment!! The customer service is great, and the food is really really really good! I wouldnt hesitate twice to get the fried shrimp. The salmon,grits, and shrimp.. lastly the seafood pasta was really good as well!
A bit slow on the service but the food was great and really flavorful, be prepared to loosen the waistband when you eat though

My friend introduced me to this spot and after viewing their IG page I was ready to taste their food. I ordered the chicken and waffles plate. While I was disappointed that I did not enjoy my plate (chicken tenders were really dry and lacked taste), my friend enjoyed his burger, and the service really made up for it. The person that cashed me out was professional, friendly and aware that my order took a little bit of time to be made; I appreciated that he apologized and continued to update me until my order came out.  I could tell the vibe of this spot would be really good once the pandemic slows down and will definitely visit again to give them another chance to earn a 5-star review.

My order came out close to the time I was told. One of the cooks came out of the kitchen pants hanging below his bottom and not organized.  No utensils with my food no napkins nothing. Customer service very lacking. Tried it once.
Black Owned Business....Really great food.
Got my order wrong & doesn’t answer their phone

It would be nice if the hours of operation on the website were updated and accurate. I was under the impression that the establishment closed at 7 PM only to show up and see that the information on the door did not match up.
I ordered breakfast from this place the food was old, sour and spoiled. Never again!
Great food just dont be in a hurry to get it
Tried the grilled cheese burger. Flavor was excellent,  burger could be a little bigger.  Fries were delicious as well. Definitely coming back
Great food!

Ordered their food on Uber Eats. Wonderful experience. Was absolutely delicious. I ordered #1. Salmon/Shrimp with Grits and #2. Chicken and Waffles. Would highly recommend #1!  Only problem is that I ordered lemonade which they (or the uber driver) forgot to include in my delivery.

Just an overall good place to get some home hearty food from the allday breakfast selection to the specials they put together for lunch and dinner and the  portions are unmatched  the hand crafted food is always on point and pretty much seasoned thoroughly
They are extremely slow. Please have 30 mins to wait on food. The food is good,  but they are slow every single time.
I love this place!!! Their food is delicious every time and the service is impeccable. They sell one of the BEST macaroni cheese I’ve ever had in my life. 100% endorse.
The seasonings will make you slap your mama tht place is is the  Bomb
Delicious Breakfast
Food was very tasty and service was quick. Looking forward to visiting again!
Patiently waited for 30 minutes, just to find out the cashier forgot to put my order in.  I just asked for a refund and left.  They need a better tracking system for order. I will not be returning.
Food was good. Staff was friendly. Price to quantity seems a little off but was delicious none the less. Would recommend

I went there with two other people and we purchased the jerk chicken, lasagna, pork ribs BBQ and the fry jumbo shrimp but, the jumbo shrimp were small and over breaded and tasted like thay baked too long now the food was good on flavor but, portion of the food very small..,. The people there are very friendly.
What more can you ask for. Shrimp and Grits that were amazing great service place was spotless good vibes!  I’ll make the stop every time I’m in town.

A Place to Walk to occupies the space of a former Five Guys. Whether you intentionally stop by or inadvertently stop in, you won’t be disappointed. The food feels like home and the staff feels like family. I encourage you to take a friend and try multiple items, or at least order something for now and something for later. My vagueness on food descriptions is because all of it is good. If you have the opportunity to stay and sit, you are guaranteed to leave with your stomach and soul full.

I tried this new spot with a few friends so we could try different things on the menu. We got the chicken & waffles, shrimp & salmon grits, fish and chips, and the jerk wings & mac. Yes, we wanted to try it all! And I’m glad we did. The jerk wings were bomb, they had a lil kick but not too spicy. The salmon was probably my favorite. It was nice and flavorful and cooked perfectly. They’ve done a great job creating a special recipe for everyone’s daily favorite dishes. I hope to see this place around for a while because I’ll definitely be going back.
Food is awesome!!!!

I am pretty picky when it comes to my food, especially breakfast, my favorite meal of the day. Where to start. My favorite thing right now is their breakfast sandwiches. Both bacon and sasuge, with turkey alternatives for both, are so freaken good. Kudos to them for making these bomb breakfast sandwiches.  The meats are cooked well and taste better. Eggs any way you like. Waffle batter is good. Grits were good. Mixed with cheese, salt and pepper, however a bit peppery, but good none the less. Its at a good location and essy to find. The staff is very nice and patient. Its only 3 of them back there, so they properly prepare each order so that everyone receives the same quality of food, which hasnt diminished so far. So there is a small wait if there is a line, but totally worth the wait.  I havent tried out their lunch items yet, but definitely gonna try and review them at a later date. I will mention that the pricing is fair, but can quickly become expensive with add-ons. The meals feel proportionate. The platters are big and filling. No real complaints there. As far as breakfast goes, i highly recommend visiting.
Their shrimp and grits is to die for the flavor is so impeccable.

I went during the grand opening week. I had the fried chicken sandwich and the shrimp and grits. All I can say is wow. From the moment i walked in the door i felt like family and the food can you say amazing! Def a hidden secret right now that won’t be for too long.
